bento.bio.accelerationist.message: I consider myself an accelerationist. Right now I focus on oss/acc (build more, ship more, talk more open source!) — I built some successful OSS projects, one even getting me MikeRoweSofted. Eventually I want to expand to nuc/acc, bme/acc, med/acc, and sci/acc.

bento.bio.medicalAI.message: I work on MLOps for a Medical AI company, building automation software that tackles medical AI challenges. I want to contribute to a better ecosystem by creating competitive global products and potentially open-sourcing them.

bento.bio.lateralThinking.message: I love lateral thinking and crazy ideas. "Rockets are too expensive" → "Just land them and reuse them." Paired with exceptional engineering, lateral thinking makes breakthroughs regardless of field.

bento.bio.earlyAdopter.message: I am an early adopter who loves trying half-baked products and early-stage prototypes. We must explore fresh ideas as scientists and engineers. Someone needs to fund them, and that better be me!

bento.bio.koreanCulture.message: I love Korean culture and K-pop, but my genuine interest lies in traditional Korean cultures. My favorite folklore is Bulgasari (불가사리), a metal-eating fire-bending beast that ended war and suffering. My favorite artifact is Jangseung (a.k.a. Beoksu), a totem pole guarding well-being.

bento.bio.noEnglishName.message: I don't have an English name, even while studying in the US. As Kihong Lee and Uzoamaka Aduba put it: "If they can learn to speak Tchaikovsky, Michelangelo, and Dostoevsky, they can learn to say your name."

bento.bio.koreanHistory.message: I love Korean history and East Asian geopolitics. I feel turbulence whenever I dive into any span of Korea's 5,000-year history, watching how our people saved themselves or screwed up. History rhymes, so better be prepared!

bento.bio.trading.message: I trade a lot. I ranked 1st on stock leaderboards on Toss Securities (Korean Robinhood). These days I study algorithmic trading strategies — sometimes Simons, sometimes Newton myself. Not a millionaire yet, but I'm on my way!

bento.bio.consoleGamer.message: I am a heavy console gamer, especially story-rich games or games with great soundtracks. Story games are the 21st-century evolution of great literature. Knowing how to savor a good game is a skill and privilege.

bento.bio.favoriteGames.message: My favorite games are Ghost of Tsushima & Yotei, Death Stranding 1 & 2, Detroit: Become Human, Expedition 33, and Sanabi. Recently obsessed with Rhythm Heaven on Wii, DS, and Gameboy. I guess I love games with great music!

bento.bio.a11yI18n.message: I am obsessed with Accessibility and Internationalization. I've seen talented friends miss opportunities due to linguistic barriers. The linguistic barrier in tech is the new unintentional Apartheid.

bento.bio.heroes.message: I love talking to intelligent people and making myself the dumbest in the room. I want to build products based on exceptional quality, not hype. My heroes: Jen-Hsun Huang (perseverance), Lisa Tzwu-Fang Su (messianic leadership), and Guillermo Rauch (bold manifesto to rectifying the future).

bento.bio.medici.message: I dream of becoming the Medici of Science & Technology. The Medici patronized brilliant people during the Renaissance and revolutionized art. I want to gather talented individuals to forge the future together, creating an ecosystem where people can freely enjoy new adventures.
